istant\",\n          \"content\": [],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 0,\n            \"output\": 0,\n            \"totalTokens\": 0,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"error\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776149379378,\n          \"errorMessage\": \"500 {\\\"error\\\":{\\\"message\\\":\\\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\\\"}}\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"b9bd4691\",\n            \"seq\": 60\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-TroLy\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 0,\n            \"output\": 0,\n            \"totalTokens\": 0,\n            \"cacheRead\": 0,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"error\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776149395467,\n          \"errorMessage\": \"500 {\\\"error\\\":{\\\"message\\\":\\\"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'providerSpecificData')\\\"}}\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"c3562531\",\n            \"seq\": 61\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492\",\n      \"kind\": \"group\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"telegram\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-ahv-dtlx-ecosystem\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:-5168104492\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776149745792,\n      \"sessionId\": \"b90d0cbf-72bc-4ccf-b0a9-5bf84f42e416\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 53121,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776149651491,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776149739320,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 87829,\n      \"childSessions\": [\n        \"agent:prompt-optimizer:subagent:0eb3c914-87cc-4bdd-9ee9-20aa3e6473e1\",\n        \"agent:senior-backend:subagent:ce81d04d-cc26-4b7d-82f4-704a8256c73b\",\n        \"agent:senior-backend:subagent:e3ca11a2-c1e6-4d1d-9d7c-680d2d0d259a\",\n        \"agent:senior-backend:subagent:2e5ea409-572b-4929-8001-fa602be9c6d2\",\n        \"agent:senior-frontend:subagent:05e6701d-36aa-491c-ab9d-8edd7eeb37f8\"\n      ],\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:-5168104492\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"main_bot\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/b90d0cbf-72bc-4ccf-b0a9-5bf84f42e416.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I have the full picture:\\n\\n**DTLX BE on port 3001 — Status:**\\n\\n✅ **Working (200):** roles, agents, courses, vehicles (4/16)\\n\\n❌ **403 Forbidden (permission denied):** users/role, users/teachers, users/students, users/sales, lessons, student-infos, work-calendars, exams, stadiums, payments, notify-configs, notify-contents (12/16)\\n\\nThe JWT bug is FIXED (id field is in the token payload). The issue now is **permission/authorization** — the `admin2` user doesn't have the right permissions to access most endpoints.\\n\\n\\nThis points to a role/permission configuration problem rather than an authentication one, which is what the previous test session found when it noted the JWT bug but didn't document the full permissions issue. The server's been running continuously on port 3001 since it started earlier, and I've been monitoring it.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Bây giờ em có bức tranh toàn cảnh. DTLX BE đang **running trên port 3001**, và đây là kết quả test đầy đủ:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🌐 DTLX BE — Status Report | 06:53 UTC 14 Apr\\n\\n### ✅ Server Running\\n- **Port:** 3001 (PID 122018)\\n- **JWT bug `doc.id`:** ✅ **ĐÃ FIX** — token payload có `id` field đúng\\n- **Login:** ✅ Hoạt động tốt với `admin2`\\n\\n### 📊 API Test Results (18 endpoints — MEMORY.md baseline)\\n\\n| Endpoint | Status | Ghi chú |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `POST /auth/signin` | ✅ 200 | Login OK |\\n| `GET /roles` | ✅ 200 | |\\n| `GET /agents` | ✅ 200 | |\\n| `GET /courses` | ✅ 200 | |\\n| `GET /vehicles` | ✅ 200 | |\\n| `GET /users/role` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /users/teachers` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /users/students` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /users/sales` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /lessons` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /student-infos` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /work-calendars` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /exams` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /stadiums` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /payments` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /notify-configs` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /notify-contents` | ❌ **403** | Không có quyền |\\n| `GET /guests` | ✅ 200 | Public — không cần auth |\\n\\n### 🔴 Root Cause — Permission/Role Configuration\\n`admin2` được seed nhưng **không có role/permission gán đúng** trong database. Các endpoint nghiệp vụ (users, lessons, exams, payments...) đều check permission middleware và trả 403.\\n\\n### ✅ Đã xác định path fix:\\n```\\n1. Gán role_id cho admin2 trong MongoDB\\n2. Hoặc tạo seed role mặc định cho admin2\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Pipeline:** HEALTHY ✅\\n**Blocker:** Cần fix permission seed cho admin2 — cần lead quyết định approach (seed script hay manual DB update).\\n\\nLead muốn fix permission bằng cách nào?\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 269,\n            \"output\": 886,\n            \"totalTokens\": 54007,\n            \"cacheRead\": 51905,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 947,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776149714071,\n          \"responseId\": \"062d17d30ee320bb036e66e89f6f4c0c\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"be602c5c\",\n            \"seq\": 21\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"label\": \"DTLX Full API Test + Seed\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776142955056,\n      \"sessionId\": \"c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 34167,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"failed\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776142852138,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776143118533,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 164345,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/c8fccefe-9951-44cf-b292-b5b8ca77a0cf.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"It seems mongosh might not be available or the database connection is different. Let me check:\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_1\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"command\": \"which mongosh mongo 2>/dev/null; mongosh --version 2>/dev/null; mongo --version 2>/dev/null\"\n              }\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_wpt5k1bnm0z3_2\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"command\": \"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/config/database.ts 2>/dev/null || cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-backend/.env 2>/dev/null | grep -i mongo | head -5\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 103,\n            \"output\": 160,\n            \"totalTokens\": 34327,\n            \"cacheRead\": 33786,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 278,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776143078585,\n          \"responseId\": \"062cfde71d5ac410f718cc52b0203c0d\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"ede613bc\",\n            \"seq\": 72\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"label\": \"DTLX BE Start & Test\",\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-subagent-53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776142006662,\n      \"sessionId\": \"da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 34224,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776141563990,\n      \"endedAt\": 1776141938964,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 351405,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"medium\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/da8cc51e-e69c-4441-b358-faff21dd6739.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Guests endpoint works without auth. Now let me also test the ping endpoint.\\n\\nLet me also check the /docs endpoint for Swagger UI.\\n\\nNow let me summarize what I've found:\\n\\n1. **Server Status**: Already running on ports 3001 (HTTP) and 5557 (Socket IO)\\n2. **MongoDB**: Connected (docker-proxy on 27017)\\n3. **Auth API**:\\n   - ✅ `POST /api/v1/auth/signin` - Works perfectly. Returns JWT tokens (access + refresh)\\n   - ❌ `POST /api/v1/auth/register` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\\n   - ❌ `GET /api/v1/auth/profile` - **Does NOT exist** in the codebase\\n4. **Guests API** (no auth required):\\n   - ✅ `GET /api/v1/guests` - Works (empty list)\\n5. **Protected endpoints**: All require auth (401 returned without token)\\n\\nThere's a bug in the token generation where `doc.id` is undefined for Mongoose lean docs, causing the `id` field to be omitted from JWT tokens. This prevents protected endpoints from working with the generated tokens, so the profile endpoint can't be tested. The auth middleware issue is a known bug where the `doc.id` field is undefined in lean queries, causing protected endpoints to fail. The register and profile endpoints don't actually exist in the codebase—the API only has signin available, so I'll document what I actually found rather than trying to force tests for non-existent routes.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\nidation\\n   - Uses encrypted data for FE attendance\\n\\n4. **Checkins module:**\\n   - Good separation between Schedule and Abnormal checkin\\n   - validateCreatorInParticipants is a private method\\n   - Good validation of time constraints\\n   - Overall clean architecture\\n\\n5. **OKRs module:**\\n   - Extremely complex aggregation pipeline in getOKRByFilter - lots of nested logic\\n   - No DRY violations detected\\n   - Good RBAC\\n\\n6. **Leave Requests module:**\\n   - 656 lines in leaveRequests.service.ts - VERY LARGE\\n   - Two-level approval workflow (Manager + HR)\\n   - Good leave balance management\\n   - Good notification system\\n   - Some DRY issues: repeated employee lookup, approval logic patterns\\n\\n7. **Auth module:**\\n   - Good token management (access + refresh)\\n   - Cookie-based refresh token\\n   - Solid implementation overall\\n\\n8. **Roles/Permissions module:**\\n   - Proper use of transactions for consistency\\n   - Redis caching for permissions with cache-busting on updates\\n   - Service instantiates itself with PermissionService.callingPermissionMaps preventing race conditions\\n\\n9. **Niko modules:**\\n   - Emotion: Good service\\n\\n, well-structured\\n   - Orders: Uses transactions properly for complex operations\\n   - Wallets: Good balance tracking\\n   - Criteria: Has try-catch with generic error rethrow - not ideal\\n   - Gifts: Good but has hardcoded 'PENDING' string (magic number)\\n   - Cart: Clean service\\n\\n**FE (React/TypeScript/RTK Query):**\\n\\n1. **API files:**\\n   - Good use of RTK Query with providesTags/invalidatesTags\\n   - Some use of `any` types (attendanceApi, okrApi, leaveApi)\\n   - Proper use of overrideExisting\\n\\n2. **AccountPage.tsx:**\\n   - 413 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Good separation of concerns with multiple forms\\n   - Clean TypeScript usage\\n   - No loading states, error handling, or prop drilling issues\\n\\n3. **EmployeePage.tsx:**\\n   - 311 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Clean patterns with hooks like usePermission, AccessControl\\n   - Good use of memoization\\n\\n4. **NikoPage.tsx:**\\n   - 779 lines - VERY LARGE, should be split into sub-components\\n   - Hardcoded emotion data in component (should be from API)\\n   - EMOTION_MAP created in render body\\n\\nNow I'm identifying the critical issues. The attendance module has massive code duplication across multiple files, the leaveRequests service is oversized at 656 lines, and there are hardcoded magic strings scattered throughout. The NikoPage component at 779 lines needs refactoring into smaller pieces. Beyond that, I'm seeing `any` types leaking across the FE API files, missing JSDoc comments in most places, and inconsistent error handling with empty catch blocks in some niko services. There's also mixed language usage between Vietnamese and English that should be standardized, and some files have unnecessary complexity that could be simplified.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Now I have enough data to write the comprehensive code quality report. Let me create it:\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_4mi0q9it66m6_1\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n           